body:
This city’s killing me. I want, I want, I want everything. This city’s killing me, In the heat of Los Angeles.

Epilogue: Landslide (Fleetwood Mac)

“I feel like we just did this,” Harry said as he pulled me into him in the back of the car.“We pretty much did. Three weeks ago.” I rested my head on his shoulder and watched the street fly by…

summary: could you maybe write husband!harry saying something like "I'm your husband" during an argument thank you 💖
question: could you maybe write husband!harry saying something like "I'm your husband" during an argument thank you 💖
answer:
Who else do you stan beside harry and one direction? I Stan Shawn mendes, he’s basically my second husband lol.

Talk to me or request for blurbs anytime here.

——

The aroma of boiled chicken and soup that had Rose Mary and pepper once watered her mouth leaving her craving for more, now was nothing but disgusting. The smell of it was enough to give missus a head ache and nausea with the taste of vomit in her throat. It was a clear signal how baby inside her womb wasn’t in favour of the having the soup it’s father made with so much of love.

They said pregnancy came along food cravings and mood swings that far by now was understood by her. One moment she’s all laughing and cuddling Harry and the next huffing and puffing because her boobs hurts. It was all weird but at the end of the day the couple were grateful and thanking god for blessing them with a baby.

“Cmon open up now lovie.” Harry cooed bringing the spoonful of soup and bits of chicken to her mouth. Anne said how soup helped to keep mother and baby healthy.

“No harry. It makes me sick.”

“Please bubba? For me?” Harry smiled a bit hoping she’d give in for the last spoon, and a sigh left past his lips when she opened her mouth taking in the warm famous of the soup, the taste of pepper hits back of her throat as she swallows.

The spoon clinks with the glass bowl as harry puts it down on the coffee table before he scoops her up in his arms so that her legs are placed on his thighs and head resting on his shoulder.

Harry’s hand cradles the five months old bumps in his hands feeling the swell and the curves—smiling to self as he remembers how their baby is resting inside.

“Um harry?” She asks pulling away a bit to look at him.

“Yes?” He asks placing a small kiss on her forehead.

“Uh you see Lucy is coming around this month and I was thinking if I could go to see her and dr-“

“No.”

“What?” She furrows her eyebrows and scoots a bit away so that she can clearly have a look on his face. He seemed a bit annoyed of course, she was putting this topic in front of him for the third time after he denied it. He wasn’t having it, his wife—being pregnant and traveling alone with her friend who didn’t seem like good peers to him.

“You can’t say no to me harry! “ she raised her voice standing up making harry turn his head to her. It wasn’t anything new for him, the sudden mood swings were a common now.

“I can. I did. You are NOT going out with Lucy or whatever her name is. She’s not a good company.” He made it clear before getting up from the couch, picking the dirty bowl and tuning on his heels to the kitchen but she wasn’t done yet. Holding his elbow he turn him around with a one swift motion.

“Who the hell are you to decide what I do and what not?!” She asked full of rage.

All the times she shouted at him out of no where didn’t bother harry at all. He very much was aware of the fact that it was just the baby but now, it was too much for him. Harry wanted nothing but to protect them both from the world.

“I’m your husband!!”

Harry raised his voice enough to get the point and not scare her.

“I-I just want to go out and have fun harry. I miss it.” She mumbles looking away. It broke his heart when she wiped a drop of tear that slide down his cheek and instantly pulled her to him kissing her head multiple times.

“I know and I’m sorry baby, but Lucy is not good. I will take you out yeah? We can bring gem and your sister along too.” He offered cupping her face and kissing her nose as he wiped her wet eyes.

“Okay.”
